&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot; data-leveltext=&quot;&quot; data-font=&quot;Symbol&quot; data-listid=&quot;12&quot; data-list-defn-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335552541&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559684&amp;quot;:-2,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:1080,&amp;quot;335559991&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;469769226&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Symbol&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469769242&amp;quot;:[8226],&amp;quot;469777803&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777804&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777815&amp;quot;:&amp

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Owner Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Hartsdale, New York&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Become a Practice Owner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a DVM aspiring to become a practice owner. Hartsdale Veterinary Hospital is looking for the right veterinarian to step into a partnership role with the opportunity to grow into co-ownership alongside Veterinary Practice Partners (VPP).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role offers the chance to step into leadership, build ownership, and help shape what comes next for a well-established hospital in a highly desirable Westchester County location. As a Partner DVM, you will help guide the practice’s direction, support the team, and play a meaningful role in its long-term success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will not just practice in the hospital.&lt;br&gt;You will help shape it and share in its success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hartsdale Veterinary Hospital is a full-service, AAHA-accredited hospital right in the heart of Hartsdale, just steps from the Metro-North train station, making it an easy commute whether you&#39;re coming from the city or nearby Westchester communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We care for a loyal and long-standing client base across Scarsdale, Edgemont, White Plains, and beyond, with a caseload that keeps things interesting, from preventative care and diagnostics to surgery and dentistry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team here is what really makes it special. It’s collaborative, well-supported, and genuinely enjoys working together. With a strong staff-to-doctor ratio, you can focus on practicing great medicine while also stepping into leadership, mentoring, and helping shape what comes next.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There’s already a strong foundation in place. It’s now ready for the right person to step in and take it forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Area&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hartsdale offers the best of both worlds, a suburban lifestyle with direct access to New York City via Metro-North. Westchester County is known for its excellent schools, vibrant communities, and proximity to dining, culture, and outdoor recreation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A great place to put down roots while still having the city within reach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What to Expect&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compensation: Competitive base salary plus production, profit participation, and long-term ownership opportunity&lt;br&gt;Location: Hartsdale, NY&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Schedule that respects your time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong staff to doctor ratio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health, dental, and vision insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employer retirement plan contribution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous PTO plus CE time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual CE allowance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relocation assistance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Licensing, DEA, AVMA PLIT, AVMA, and VIN covered&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ownership and Partnership with VPP&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Veterinary Practice Partners supports doctor-led hospitals. We do not rebrand your practice. Hartsdale Veterinary Hospital remains locally branded and reflective of your leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Partner DVM, you will have the opportunity to participate in a structured co-ownership model with meaningful ownership and defined participation in performance and growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You lead the medicine. VPP provides operational, financial, HR, recruiting, and marketing support so you can focus on clinical excellence and team development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VPP supports more than 190 hospitals nationwide and over 200 doctor partners, including more than 100 first time veterinary owners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ndependence Veterinary Clinic is seeking a part-time Dog Bather &lt;/strong&gt;to join our caring and dedicated team. This role plays an important part in supporting our grooming department and ensuring pets feel clean, comfortable, and safe throughout their grooming experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What to Expect&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As you join our mission, expect to be supported in your work and home life with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employee referral bonus. &lt;/strong&gt;Earn $1,000 when you refer a new team member to one of our 180+ partner hospitals across the country.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opportunity to gain hands-on grooming experience and grow within the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: &lt;/strong&gt;$15.00&amp;nbsp; per hour, determined by the candidate&#39;s skills, experience, and qualifications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Monday- Friday 8:30 am-3 pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bathing and drying dogs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nail trims&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Teeth brushing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ear cleaning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brushing and basic coat care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting groomer as needed and maintaining a clean work area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring pets are handled calmly and safely at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience working with dogs and cats required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grooming experience is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort handling dogs and cats of various sizes and temperaments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and cleanliness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dependable, team-oriented, and able to follow instructions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re making an investment in the next generation of veterinary doctors!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the professional veterinary curriculum, colleges encourage off-campus educational experiences in practices outside of the teaching hospital. Practical experience in a well-run and contemporary practice can be a valuable component of your veterinary education, preparing you to deliver better care after graduation. Our program is dedicated to contributing to your practice-readiness and to help you hit the ground running after graduation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our program structure:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our externships are flexible—they can range from two to eight weeks during the year, according to your college curriculum – but are typically two or three weeks in length.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our externship rotations are designed to allow students, under veterinary supervision, to practice the problem-solving, technical and communication skills that they have acquired during their clinical preparation. Externs are given the opportunity to work alongside our veterinary team and are encouraged to participate in all aspects of patient care.&amp;nbsp;A stipend of $250 per week will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Externs experience the typical caseload of a small animal practice. Under the supervision of your mentor doctor you will gather histories, perform physical examinations, develop diagnostic and therapeutic plans, scrub in to surgery, assist in the management of medical cases, provide wellness care, develop your client communication skills, polish your technical skills and produce appropriate medical records (SOAPs) within the time limits of daily practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Commitment to Diversity:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;We are dedicated to establishing a culture that celebrates all forms of diversity and allows us to be an inclusive service provider in this &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;community.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we&#39;re looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Extern students are expected to be enthusiastic and effective participants in our patient care activities, upholding the professional and ethical standards of our practice. Students participating in the externship program are suggested to review the Veterinary Practice Act in regard to the scope of duties that may be performed, and to be familiar with the type and degree of veterinary supervision that is required. These should be followed carefully in order to protect both yourself and our practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a veterinary student extern, we expect you to dress and behave in a professional manner and to meet the expectations that we have of all team members as outlined in our employee handbook.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be enrolled in an accredited DVM program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are authorized to work in the United States.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must carry professional liability insurance. AVMA PLIT liability insurance is free for all student members of the AVMA. You may apply for this coverage on their &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.avmaplit.com/products/student-liability/&quot;&gt;website&lt;/a&gt;. Please check to make sure your coverage is current and submit a certificate of coverage with your application.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As sponsors of the Veterinary Externship Program, we see ourselves to be part of your educational team, providing instruction, mentoring and evaluation of the students who participate. You will be assigned a mentor and work on the learning objectives as defined by your college program or to meet your specific goals. At the end of the externship your mentor will pro

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hospital Assistant&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Salary: &lt;/strong&gt;$17.13 - $17.90 per hour (based on experience and qualifications)&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Schedule: &lt;/strong&gt;Monday - Friday, rotating weekends&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Horse Heaven Hills Pet Urgent Care and Veterinary Center is hiring Hospital Assistants to work alongside our team of experienced veterinarians, skilled technicians, and devoted support staff to ensure each animal receives the best possible care. If you are enthusiastic, reliable, and excited about helping us maintain our high standards of animal care and customer service, we would love to hear from you!&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What to Expect&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;As you join our mission to provide high-quality, compassionate veterinary care when pets need it most, expect to be supported in your work and home life with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All the benefits you deserve—medical, dental, vision, retirement, PTO—plus an employee pet discount because we know your pets are family, too.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Observe and report to medical staff on health/condition of patients: food and water intake, urine color, stool characteristics, vomiting, sneezing, coughing, or any symptoms or behaviors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support LVTs and Veterinary Assistants in a variety of tests and analyses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record temperature, pulse, and respiration notes for patients under anesthesia while under direct supervision of an LVT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the acquisition of proper radiographs of patients using correct technique, while ensuring personal safety&lt;/li&gt;
