&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inventory Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary&lt;/strong&gt;: $18.00 – $25.00 per hour, determined by the candidate&#39;s skills, experience, and qualifications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule&lt;/strong&gt;: Monday – Friday, 8:00 a.m. – 4:00 p.m., alternating 10:00 a.m. – 6:00 p.m. shifts, with rotating weekends. Reliability and a positive, team-oriented attitude are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fox Creek Veterinary Hospital at Wildwood is hiring a full-time Inventory Specialis&lt;/strong&gt;t to manage and maintain the hospital’s inventory systems and ensure our team has the supplies and products needed to deliver exceptional patient care. Our ideal candidate is detail-oriented, organized, and passionate about supporting a high-functioning veterinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What to Expect&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A comprehensive benefits package, including medical, dental, and vision insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid time off and a 401(k) plan for full-time employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee pet discount because we know your pets are family, too.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle purchasing activities in compliance with clinic policies and within budget, including managing purchase orders and tracking backorders and inaccuracies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain appropriate levels of quantity on hand, reorder levels, and reorder quantities in the practice management software system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee all receipts of inventory items and maintain the barcoding system with the support of the inventory assistant.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage stock rotation following the “first in, first out” method and coordinate returns of overstock, short-dated, or outdated items to vendors for credit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with weekly, monthly, quarterly, and annual inventory counts, including DEA/BNDD substance logging and audits in accordance with legal requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in updating inventory costs and pricing in software to reflect accurate product markup or margin, while identifying waste and minimizing product duplication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audit patient visit lists (PVLs) and open transactions to identify missed charges, incomplete entries, and open prescriptions that need to be restocked.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document KPIs and captured charges, guide team members as needs arise, and work with the supervisor to assess discount trends and reasons.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma required; 2-year College Degree or RVT preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of veterinary services, protocols, and products required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift 30 lbs unassisted and work on a computer for extended periods of time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills and ability to problem-solve effectively with the medical team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Fox Creek Veterinary Hospital in Wildwood, MO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fox Creek Veterinary Hospital was founded in October 2000 with the mission to provide the very best care combined with the latest and most up-to-date facilities and equipment. Our staff, as a team, is dedicated through continuing education and compassion to provide our patients with the level of care we would demand for our own pets.&amp;nbsp;As an AAHA-Accredited practice, these principles are our passion and by fulfilling them, we are living our dream of knowing that we make a difference by helping animals every day.&amp;nbsp;We are happy to see Canine, Feline, Equine, and Pocket Pets!&lt;/p&gt;
